(421, 1, '2015-08-07 11:11:19', '2015-08-07 11:11:19', 'If one happen to ask me about the best investment option for an individual, my reply would be Public Provident Fund (PPF). A risk-free return of 8.70% p.a. (as notified presently by the Government) and that too tax-free. What more do you want!\r\n\r\nPPF scheme is a long-term investment scheme backed by the Government of India. It offers safety with attractive interest rate and returns that are fully exempt from tax. The interest on the PPF account is notified by the Government at the beginning of every year and the current rate of interest is 8.70%.\r\n\r\nAn individual can invest as low as Rs. 500/- upto Rs. 1,50,000/- per annum. Contribution made to PPF account is eligible for rebate u/Sec. 88 of the Income Tax Act. The tenure of PPF account is fixed at 15 years, and can be extended for a further block of 5 years.\r\n\r\n An annual investment of Rs.1,00,000/- per annum in PPF account will grow to Rs. 31,17,276/- if the current interest rate of 8.70% is maintained.', 'Why Invest in PPF ?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'why-invest-in-ppf', '', '', '2015-08-07 11:11:19', '2015-08-07 11:11:19', '', 0, 'http://webphics.com/wordpress/wp_dalmiablog/?p=421', 0, 'post', '', 0),
